# Code Conventions

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Prefer named exports; default exports are allowed for existing/legacy modules or where
  justified (e.g., `React.memo` wrappers). New files should use named exports unless there
  is a clear reason not to.
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## How to Verify

### Components

```bash
# Confirm no class components exist
grep -rn "extends React\.Component\|extends Component\|extends PureComponent" packages/ --include="*.tsx" --include="*.ts"
# Expected: no output

# Audit default exports in new component files (existing files are exempt)
# Prefer named exports for new code; flag unexpected new default exports for review
grep -rn "^export default" packages/ --include="*.tsx"
# Expected: only legacy/existing files — new files should use named exports
```

### TypeScript

```bash
# TODO: Update to skip comment lines.
grep -rn ": any\b\|as any\b" packages/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"
# Expected: no output

# Confirm no @ts-ignore usage
grep -rn "@ts-ignore" packages/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"
# Expected: no output
```

### Files

```bash
# Find component files not following PascalCase convention
find packages/ -name "*.tsx" | grep -v "__tests__" | grep -v ".test." | grep -vE "/[A-Z][A-Za-z0-9]+\.tsx$"
# Expected: no output (all .tsx files should be PascalCase)

# Find non-component TS files not following kebab-case convention
find packages/ -name "*.ts" |  grep -v ".d.ts" | grep -vE "(__tests__|test)" | grep -vE "/[a-z][a-z0-9-]+\.ts$"
# Expected: no output
```
